<br>
The &quot;dude&quot; in SolB &quot;should&quot; spawn once every day. It appears as though VI F'd up, and the spawn time is MUCH longer. You hand him your pearl, and get another back, thus de-spawning the mob.<br>
<br>
There is no &quot;triggered&quot;. They are completely independant events, not linked in any way. Not sure where people got this from. The patch from VI did not say they were linked.<br>
<br>
You can do either in any order. ie, you could if you really wanted to do RF first of all your Epic pieces.<br>
<br>
The 2nd Zord in SF is supposed to be on a 3 day timer, random. Again, VUI F'd it up so that at first he was not spawning at all. Clerics quickly noticed, and so the zone was brought down server wide, probably putting the mob on the spawn table, so he spawns now... finally.<br>
<br>
There is no &quot;handing in&quot; for the 2nd Zord in SF. You just kill him, and this spawns RF, who you kill.<br>
<br>
The Zord in SF is KOS (not 100% sure on this..) to lots of people. He &quot;may&quot; be on Ring of Scale faction. This is a guess.<br>
<br>
This means that anyone can do Ragefire. A cleric does not even need to be there to loot the container. This &quot;may&quot; be an issue (which even VI admit) with bigger guilds farming RF not for his cleric container, but for his other drops (CoF !!).<br>
<br>
When handing in, there is more than just the heart to do. There are other items.<br>
<br>
However in the end, I defer to a cleric who has actually done it to confirm this.<br>
